  </sponsors>
  <source>Fraunhofer-Institute of Toxicology and Experimental Medicine</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It's the aim of this study to clarify, whether the non-invasive assessment of breath can
      serve as a novel clinical tool to assist in the diagnosis of CLAD. If different stages of BOS
      can be discriminated by the level of certain VOCs than there would also be a potential to
      actually predict the development at an early stage and would enable an earlier intervention.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
